title: In and Out
body:
Pairing: Tony Stark x Reader

Warnings: Canonical violence and banter/language

Summary: Usually, you’re careful not to get involved with “teams” so you can work alone but a certain Avenger in red and gold has caught your attention. When curiosity crosses the line into borderline obsession, you take more risks than you should and land yourself right in the situation you swore you never wanted to be in. While you wonder if it was worth it, it becomes apparent you weren’t the only one obsessed.

title: Marvel's Cinematic Translation Errors
body:
BW Media Spotlight checks out Marvel’s Cinematic Translation Errors

(psst…that’s the real Yondu in the back)

One of the strengths of the Marvel Cinematic Universe over the recent DC films is that the MCU is willing to embrace the comic book nature of the source material (comic books…duh) and stay relatively true to those characters, with minor differences. Most of the time. There are also some major changes as the screenwriters and directors will often change…

title: Just Like That Bluebird
body:
read it on the AO3 at http://bit.ly/2WUpi4y

by Former_Heroes

Tony Stark hasn’t left the house in six months. It’s definitely not because of his anxiety or PTSD or Loki anything. He’s working on saving the world.

Steve Rogers is a retired from active military service. He is. He’s just helping a friend out, and stopping a couple of terrorists.

But when danger looms over New York in a force the likes of which no one has seen before, they team up with a bunch of maladjusted misfits to save the world. But with drama, mental health diagnoses and budding attractions brewing among the group, nothing will ever be easy for them.

Also, Loki is not a traitor to the Asgardian crown whatsoever, no matter what everyone thinks.

body:
Arc reactor tattoo

So been itching to get another tattoo for years and just not settled on one. Was debating obviously avengers one the other night and I was gonna do a mash up of Tony’s arc reactor and Steve’s shield but couldn’t doodle anything into something I wanted. So think I’m gonna get one of each 😅

The problem now is which arc reactor to choose: the 1st, 2nd or 3rd one? I know I don’t want the infinity war nanotech one, I just didn’t like the overall shape of it.

I’m kinda leaning towards the 1st one as it was proof that Tony Stark is who he is: a genius, a hero and did not give up in that cave but came out stronger. But I just can’t settle… What do you guys think?

summary: A Second Chance (To Get It Right)
title: A Second Chance (To Get It Right)
body:
read it on the AO3 at http://bit.ly/2uZbBoQ

blog.description: An Iron Man fan in mourning. Thank you, my darling. We'll all take care of Morgan for you. I love you 3000.

summary:
Either I'm a fucking idiot, or the cinema I bought Endgame tickets from fucked up.....Pretty sure I'm just an idiot.
I thought I...
body:
Either I’m a fucking idiot, or the cinema I bought Endgame tickets from fucked up…..Pretty sure I’m just an idiot.

I thought I had found tickets for Endgame the day before the release.

Turns out it’s just a rerun of Infinity War….not my brightest moment, I must admit.

So, I’m seeing Infinity War on the 23rd and Endgame on the 24th…..Not the worst outcome, I suppose…
